rComments: She's an amazing person that really cares about her students. Her lectures are straight forward and interesting to listen to. Test and exam are hard but if you do all the readings and go to all classes you should be just fine. (Exam jam session was super helpful
She's simply brilliant. She's also dedicated. 3
Amazing person! Anybody that is fortunate enough to have her should count their blessings. I graduated from UofT a few years ago and still miss her classes. Truly inspiring!!!

Great professor, kept me interested and engaged. Extremely knowledgable, friendly and available. Helps if you're genuinely interested in the material. Just be prepared to put in as much an effort as she does! Her classes aren't a walk in the park. This is university, after all.
Super engaging and really funny. Her obsession with bums made everyone smile. She talks really fast but I had no issue keeping up so long as I paid attention

Phenomenal. Took into to 20th C in my first year. Received a B in intro and an -A in this 2nd year class. Why? Alison is interesting and really knows her stuff. I was never bored and she stars all of the slides that you need to know for exams so although she may cover a lot and she may speak quickly you only NEED to take notes on marked slides

amazing woman, very encouraging, never makes you feel dumb. Amazingly accessible over email. show her that you care about doing well by visiting office hours and DO THE READINGS!! ppl that don't read in 3/ 4th yr class have nothing to talk about and this is frustrating for her. Hilarious woman, I feel privileged to have known her.
she talks too fast and wastes time.
She is it ! Everything you wish for.  Very inspiring.
She speaks WAY too fast! You don't have time to look at the slides, because by the time you write half a sentence down, she changes the image.  It's very hard to learn anything in her class.

Art Theory is such an intense course but she makes it enjoyable. I actually look forward to class. She's a little quirky but she's extremely smart.  She cares a lot about her students and will make sure that everyone understands.  When a prof puts that much effort into teaching, the student wants to try even harder.  I know I do.  :)

A wonderful professor. True, she does speed through lectures, but I have never had a problem keeping up with notes. It is difficult to cram so much into a lecture, and not go through it quickly. She is incredibly helpful, sweet, and approachable.

I find that her lectures are too jam packed with monuments. I think that if she went into detail discussing specific monuments it would be more informative and beneficial to the student. I know it's hard to limit yourself when it comes to all the great art of the 20thC though. Also, quite speedy.

omg, syme is awesome. Yes, i agree with the frisky comment. "I know you all enjoyed that frisky little exam". LOL. so good. I think she's a genius though. I've never heard a more well-spoken lecturer. Very eloquent and concise. Too concise....she packs a LOT into a lecture. fast as hell. Great prof
She is such an amazing prof! Although she can talk incredibly fast, youll learn alot in her course. She even boosted my essay mark from what the TA gave me. Overall she is a really nice teacher.

She is such an amazing prof!  She makes the lectures very interesting!  She is a little speedy... but, that's good, since you won't have time to get distracted!  Not only is her wardrobe amazing but she knows her stuff, too!  She's one of my all-time fav profs!  Who else would use the word 'frisky' to describe an exam?  Hahaha :) She's my herooo
My absolute favortie professor and she's fun!! One day she was wearing professor clothes and red fishnet stockings haha.and she gives a great lecture.
